layers.name: Before the photographer arrives, the following should be taken care of:
THINGS TO CLEAN OR PUT AWAY
Clutter and normal day-to-day messes put away, such as
Shoes (including baskets of shoes by the front door or anywhere else in
Pet toys, crates, mats, and bowls
sSmall rugs if they are dirty, normally used for feet wiping, or don’t
Toiletries (toothbrushes, tissue boxes, non-décor soap dishes and
dispensers, shampoo and cream bottles in tub, shower, and countertops,
sponges, non-décor bath towels, bath robes, etc.)
Most things on the kitchen counters and any tables should be cleared
away unless it will enhance the photo.
Weight scales in bathrooms and kitchens
Try to hide electrical wires whenever possible, but don’t disconnect lighting
fixtures as we will need all the lights turned on
All trashcans inside and outside the home should be put away out of site.
Lawn care items/gardening items/hoses/general yard messes should be put
Pool toys and pool maintenance supplies including pool vacuums located inside
Bathroom mirrors should be wiped down
Bikes/golf-carts/skateboards/etc should be out of sight
Cars should be in the garage or parked down the street away from the front of
Any personal or family photos that you don’t want showing up in our photos
Controversial items (ie: nude portraits on walls  --- true story!).
Rearrange any furniture you think will look bad or remove excessive furniture.
We want to see your room! (a good rule of thumb is that bulky chair or couch
backs do not look good when they are facing the camera, we try to take
pictures of rooms looking out towards the windows and sliding glass doors, if
your furniture is arranged in a way that there will be the back of a bulky couch
or large chair facing the camera, try to move these pieces against a wall or
away from the center of the room so they are not overpowering the photo.)
Turn on all lights (including all floor and table lamps) and open all window
Put away everything outside and around the home the same way you would for
Turn on all interior lights and open all window shades the same as you would do
for daytime photos (including in the garage if the garage has a window).
In addition, we will need all outside and landscaping lights turned on.
***IF YOUR HOUSE IS VACANT, WE NEED TO KNOW WHERE THE SWITCHES FOR THE POOL
LIGHT AND ANY EXTERIOR, LANDSCAPE, OR FOUNTAIN LIGHTS ARE LOCATED
If you know that there is an angle that you want a room shot in, or there as angle that
you hate, or something that you absolutely do not want showing up in a photo, please
let the photographer know so that they can try to accommodate your request.
If you know that at some point in the near future, you will be:
Throwing out the exercise equipment that was filling the den
Cutting down a tree or changing landscaping in some way
Or doing anything else to the house that you will want to show up in the photos
Then the photo shoot needs to be scheduled after these things are done
